It has been a long time since I have watched modern network television with anything akin to pleasure.  I have always enjoyed Mark Harmon as a craftsman; he has the kind of demeanor, presence and ability that makes me think of John Wayne and smile.  Harmon's chilling deconstruction of Ted Bundy was outstanding; that film role required supreme ability due to the lack of emphasis on factual gore surrounding the serial killings and more emphasis on the actual character of Bundy.  Harmon nailed it.  More recent "Ted Bundy flicks" are nothing more than B-movie horror flicks, promoting the gore and turning the American serial killer into a minor incarnation of Michael Myers or Jason Voorhies.  His body of work might not be what I would hope for such a talented man, but his work never lies or purports to be what it is not.  So, I had certain confidence that NCIS, especially with Harmon on both sides of the camera, would be a winner.  And NCIS does rarely disappoints...especially when the episode pertains to Gibbs.  I just hope, by Season 20, that someone fills in the last missing pieces in "The Rules."

Like another review, this is about the actual disc set shipped to me, not the quality of the NCIS show itself (which is stellar, of course). This item is shown as a complete 'box set' -- that all ten seasons will be the box set style, where there are three slim DVD cases, 2 discs each, that then slide inside a heavy outer cardboard box.

What I actually received was a box set for seven of the seasons (1-6, & 10), but seasons 7, 8, and 9 were actually a completely different style -- the plastic multi-disc snap case style, where you open the snap case and then all discs are snapped into little rolodex-style plastic holders. No outer cardboard box on those three seasons.

If you want your set to all be the same for visual similarity or any other purpose, I would not recommend this set. If you are just looking to get all 10 seasons at once and don't care there's a mis-match, then I'm sure this would be just fine for you.

NCIS has some of the most different characters that comprise the top level of stars in a show without being a science fiction, historical depiction, cartoon or fantasy that I have seen.  What with a Goth-inspired laboratory specialist, happy-go-lucky (who's really not so happy), good-looking investigator, a forensics specialist who talks to his dead bodies, his assistant who cracks unfunny jokes at the wrong time, a multitude of wonderful probies, McGee and his special tech talents, and on and on... you couldn't ask for more variety in casting.  The stories are, at times, scary, heart-rending, homages to courageous military personnel and textbook examples of how to investigate crimes.  You just about have it all - especially with the wonderfully humorous carryings-on between McGee and DiNozzo.  There is something for everyone in this series.  Having all of the seasons in one set like this, you can enjoy the show without being in limbo about what happens next.  After you have finished the first 10 seasons, you are ready for the next 5 or more.  I don't think you will be disappointed in the purchase of the Ten Season Pack.
